      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks, that's a strong perspective to include. i'm curious though, when i'm presenting this to the class, how do you suggest i frame the idea of \"originalism\" in relation to this? since the debate usually boils down to whether we should follow the original intent of the founders or the living document approach, can you explain why the living document view of substantive due process is considered the more robust way to interpret the law today?",
